        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-12-09 17:50:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> (7 comments)\n> \n> minor stuff that needs to be resolved\n\nThank you for your support. Will make the changes and commit again.\nRegarding the pyyaml module, the requirements.txt file is a dictionary that is extracted from the model's metadata.json file. And Acumos is not including pyyaml, only cv, dill, acumos etc. I am not sure if the DCAE model runner included pyyaml before as this is a recent error with the current release of DCAE model runner. Currently, when the pod starts, the DCAE model runner throws an error as pyyaml module not found. I can only say that it uses pyyaml without installing it exclusively or probably assumes that the environment has pyyaml installed.",
